    "title": "Immediate Requirement Production Engineer at Nalco",
    "description": "Nalco is actively seeking a talented and motivated Production Engineer to join our dynamic team in Pimpri-Chinchwad. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout Nalco:\nNalco is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Ensure compliance with safety regulations and factory acts\n• Oversee daily production operations to meet output targets\n• Coordinate with logistics for dispatching finished goods\n• Ensure environmental compliance and waste management\n• Coordinate with design and engineering teams on product improvements\n• Train and supervise shop floor workers and supervisors\n• Prepare production cost analysis and efficiency reports\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Arch / M.Arch from recognized institution\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in ISO 9001\n• Proficiency in Project Management\n• Proficiency in PLC/SCADA\n• Proficiency in Supply Chain Management\n• Proficiency in Lean Manufacturing\n• Proficiency in Statistical Process Control\n• Proficiency in Kaizen\n• Proficiency in GD&T\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Pimpri-Chinchwad, Maharashtra, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Nalco!",
